Class Enzyme

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.bioforscher.singa.chemistry.descriptive.entities.ChemicalEntity<SimpleStringIdentifier>
      • de.bioforscher.singa.chemistry.descriptive.entities.Protein
        • de.bioforscher.singa.chemistry.descriptive.entities.Enzyme
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Annotatable, Identifiable<SimpleStringIdentifier>, Nameable, Featureable

    public class Enzyme
extends Protein
    An Enzyme is a Protein, that is associated with a catalytic function. For the usage in reactions this chemical entity can be supplied with a Michaelis constant (usually abbreviated with km), an turnover number (abbreviated with kcat), a List of possible substrates and a critical substrate that is rate determining. Additionally multiple predefined Annotations can be set (additional names, organisms, amino acid sequences, ...). Enzymes may be parsed from the UniProt Database using the UniProtParserService.
